title: Man struck, killed by train in Auburn
text:
A man was struck and killed by a train on Union Pacific Railroad tracks in Auburn Thursday morning.
Auburn police said the engineer didn’t realize the train had struck anyone until it arrived in Tacoma and evidence of a possible crash was seen on the train. There was fog in the area at the time the man was hit.
The body of a man in his 40s was then found at 29 th and Emerald Downs Way in Auburn.
He had been walking along the tracks.
A Union Pacific freight train hit & killed a man walking along the tracks in Auburn. Heavy fog to blame. pic.twitter.com/BG9Ay1HzUa
— Nick McGurk (@NickKIRO7) October 22, 2015
